### Finding A-3: Service Account Console Access Disabled — REMEDIATED

**Original finding:** IAM service account created for monitoring integration with console access enabled and no MFA enrollment. Not in IAM inventory. Not subject to quarterly review.

**Remediation decision:** Fix before authorization. This is the highest-priority Moderate finding — it represents a current active security exposure (a console-enabled account with no MFA). The remediation is operationally simple: disable console access on one IAM account. There is no reason to defer this to the POA&M.

**Remediation executed:**

*Step 1 — Disable console access:*
IT Administrator navigated to IAM console → Users → [service-account-name] → Security credentials → Console password → Disable. Verified: Console password status now shows Disabled. Timestamp: [date/time]. Change log reference: CM-CHG-[number].

*Step 2 — Verify programmatic access still functions:*
IT Administrator confirmed monitoring tool continues to operate using access keys — the tool does not use console access. Verification: monitoring tool health check shows normal operation at [date/time].

*Step 3 — Add account to IAM inventory:*
ISSO added [service-account-name] to the SSP IAM entity inventory with documentation: account purpose (monitoring integration), access type (programmatic only), key rotation schedule (annual), quarterly review inclusion: yes. SSP updated to v1.1.2. Change log reference: CM-CHG-[number].

*Step 4 — Add account to quarterly review scope:*
IAM entity inventory used for quarterly review updated to include the new entry. Next quarterly review date: [date].

**Post-remediation verification:** AWS Config rule `mfa-enabled-for-iam-console-access` — COMPLIANT as of [date]. Config compliance history shows the transition from NON_COMPLIANT to COMPLIANT with timestamp. Screenshot in remediation evidence package Section R-1.

**Assessor verification:** Remediation evidence submitted to assessor [date]. Assessor confirmed Finding A-3 resolved — SAR updated to reflect remediation status: Resolved pre-authorization.

