## Finding A-2: SSP Documentation Updated — RESOLVED

Finding A-2 (KMS root account condition not documented in SSP) was a documentation accuracy issue. No configuration change required — SSP update only.

ISSO updated SSP SC-28 implementation description to acknowledge the root account KMS condition, note that root account usage requires MFA and generates CloudTrail alerts reviewed by ISSO, and document the policy rationale (prevents permanent key inaccessibility). SSP version updated to v1.1.3. This finding is resolved — not a POA&M item.

